    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "70e46f90_f615e062",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 47,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T19:34:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I do a pass here because StringToNumber requires a perfect input, without non-matching trailing characters, and I also need the length of the number in order to advance the input past it.\n\nWe didn\u0027t want to use sscanf because of a lack of overflow detection.\n\nIt looks like strtol/strtoul provides string length and overflow detection for longs, but not ints. Do you think leveraging these and adding overflow checks for ints is a better way to go?",
      "parentUuid": "9401463a_8a49fbf8",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e8de7724_788810a3",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 47,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T19:57:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I do a pass here because StringToNumber requires a perfect input, without non-matching trailing characters, and I also need the length of the number in order to advance the input past it.\n\u003e \n\u003e We didn\u0027t want to use sscanf because of a lack of overflow detection.\n\u003e \n\u003e It looks like strtol/strtoul provides string length and overflow detection for longs, but not ints. Do you think leveraging these and adding overflow checks for ints is a better way to go?\n\nI suppose we can live with this quirk. If the pattern comes up elsewhere (and it may in other /proc files), we can revisit and factor out something common that does precisely what we need.",
      "parentUuid": "70e46f90_f615e062",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
