    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "882884b5_5ac65557",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 53,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Somewhat confusingly, we’ve got a couple of different ways to convert strings to numbers. There’s crashpad::StringToNumber\u003c\u003e(), which you’ve used here, which accepts arbitrary bases. And there’s base::StringTo*(), from base/strings/string_number_conversions.h, which accepts only decimal. The interfaces are similar.\n\nHere, since I think you’re only really concerned with decimal input, the base functions would be preferred. Except those come with the quirk that they’re not templatized, so you’d need to provide a small templatized adapter.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
