      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T19:57:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I had the initializers before as a check to see if they had been set properly, but you pointed that 0 is a valid pid and I no longer use default values to check whether they have been set. Do you think it\u0027s a good idea to set default values anyways in the event Initialize fails?\n\nWe normally do initialize all member variables of classes in Crashpad. I can see that it’s not strictly required here, but it’s good practice to help spot bugs.\n\nWhere 0 is a valid value but -1 isn’t, and that’ll be most or all cases, go with -1.",
      "parentUuid": "6b6625b1_0242da8e",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
