    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bd992491_26f15047",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 100,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "#include \u003cstdio.h\u003e for snprintf(), fopen(), getline(), etc.\n\nI’d move this snprintf() into the {scope} that follows. so that it’s closer to the fopen() that uses it. In fact, I’d even move the declaration of path[] into the scope. I know that means that you’ll duplicate it a couple of times, but it’s conceptually neater to not have path[] outlive the scope that’s associated with its FILE*.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
