    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "062c2c2c_d4905f1c",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 104,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We use PLOG() after things that fail and set errno, to provide a nicely-formatted error message.\n\nThe typical Crashpad style here would be\n\nPLOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"fopen\";\n\nWhere “path” is obvious (it will be here based on the file and line number), we’d leave it out. Otherwise, it’d just be\n\nPLOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"fopen \" \u003c\u003c path;",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7b5b0e98_4c387b76",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 112,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We’re going to want to slurp up the entire file anyhow (see the next few comments about being strict), so let’s do\n\n  ssize_t len;\n  while ((len \u003d getline(\u0026buffer, \u0026buffer_size, status_file.get())) \u003e 0) {\n    const char* line \u003d buffer;\n  }\n  if (!feof(status_file.get()) {\n    PLOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"getline\";\n    return false;\n  }\n\n(see below for why I’ve saved “len”)",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c1c9966b_67114fa4",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
