    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b2f6202f_f91ee48f",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 119,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Let’s get a little stricter with the file format, and structure it like this:\n\nif (Chomp(\u0026line, \"PPid:\\t\")) {\n  if (have_ppid) {\n    LOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"format error: multiple PPid fields\";\n    return false;\n  }\n  if (!ChompNumber(\u0026line, \u0026ppid_)) {\n    LOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"format error: unrecognized PPid format\";\n    return false;\n  }\n  have_ppid \u003d true;\n}\n\nIf there’s some reason that we can’t understand the format of the file, it can be serious, and we’d generally prefer to fail so that we can find out about the problem sooner rather than press on with questionable data.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
