        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Don’t explicitly write the template parameter when it can be inferred from the type of \u0026ppid_.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5f4b0df3_34315b86",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 121,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is quite dangerous: throughout all of this, you’re operating on “line” without regard for the line length (which I suggested you could have saved in “len” above) or even buffer_size.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "975b844c_0f4a3d2c",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 121,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T19:34:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oops, I had meant to have all the checks for null-terminators in the helper functions but looks like I didn\u0027t do that. getline promises to null-terminate its buffers. Do you think it\u0027s okay to rely on checks for nulls or check line lengths as well?",
      "parentUuid": "5f4b0df3_34315b86",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bec2fe46_551bd187",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 121,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T19:57:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Oops, I had meant to have all the checks for null-terminators in the helper functions but looks like I didn\u0027t do that. getline promises to null-terminate its buffers. Do you think it\u0027s okay to rely on checks for nulls or check line lengths as well?\n\nIf you’re just relying on NUL-termination, you’re blind to embedded NULs. If we’re being strict with formats, we want to see those (and fail due to a format error if that’s appropriate).",
      "parentUuid": "975b844c_0f4a3d2c",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "11135e87_6101ee2f",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 138,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Move the chomp from the previous line here to the while () condition. Turn the break above into a  log-and-return.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6191544f_9f02bd00",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 143,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Comments from the read of the previous file apply to the other files that you read in this function too.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "32435ddd_fbaa8769",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 151,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If getline() failed for some sort of I/O error, it’d be nice to say so. So you’d do\n\nif (length \u003c 0)\n  if (!feof(stat_file.get()) {\n    PLOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"getline\";\n  } else {\n    LOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"format error: premature EOF\";\n  }\n  return false;\n}\n\nIf you hit an early EOF,",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b92a2d1b_751a9853",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 162,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There’s a lot of - and + and redoing the same operation repeatedly in here. You can simplify:\n\n  while (--line_ptr \u003e\u003d buffer \u0026\u0026 *line_ptr !\u003d \u0027)\u0027) {}",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ea617184_ade5ee89",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 164,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "But you’ll still need to deal with the fact that the file might not have had any parentheses at all. You wouldn’t want to keep going in that case.\n\n  if (*line_ptr !\u003d \u0027)\u0027) {\n    LOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"format error\";\n    return false;\n  }",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "65623b50_152ec764",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 174,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We don’t need all of this verbosity, and we certainly don’t need to dump the remainder of the line. Just a simple \"format error\" will suffice.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "101a7f4d_51bc0c09",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 184,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Note: no need to say “struct” in C++ unless necessary to avoid an ambiguity with a function of the same name. That’s not the case here. Same on line 190.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6987dd80_3d507b67",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 185,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "#include \u003ctime.h\u003e",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b6c3cb90_fc6a84ac",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 186,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "PLOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"clock_gettime\";\n\nalso on line 192.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "511bde5e_1d1bfac6",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 198,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Make use of the nanoseconds as much as possible.\n\ntimespec boot_time;\nSubtractTimespec(\u0026current_time, \u0026uptime, \u0026boot_time);\nstart_time_.tv_sec \u003d boot_time + seconds_after_boot;\nstart_time_.tv_usec \u003d 0;\n\nUnfortunately, there’s no such thing as SubtractTimespec(), but you can provide one fairly easily. It’d be similar to timersub() from \u003csys/time.h\u003e, but operating on timespecs instead of timevals. (Some systems have timespecsub(), but not here.)",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9713187b_fc1e73c0",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 202,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "const bool, here and on line 204",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e8654bba_ff0d0d16",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 217,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The correct way to write this is to\n\n#include \"base/posix/eintr_wrapper.h\"\n\nif (HANDLE_EINTR(sys_waitpid(pid_, nullptr, __WALL)) \u003c 0) {\n  PLOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"waitpid\";\n  return false;\n}\n\nHANDLE_EINTR() takes care of the EINTR retry loop for you. You should use it any time you’re working with a system call or primitive standard library function that might return EINTR and doesn’t need careful supervision to be restarted.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "61f60714_43c5f6ff",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 230,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think that this approach will work if you’re a 64-bit process trying to read a 32-bit one, but if you’re going in the other direction, sizeof(regbuf) will be smaller than the full amount that the kernel could to return, and it’ll just fill up to that point and stop.",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cc8083dd_dc372dd6",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 230,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T19:34:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s why I added the \"extra\" char in the buffer. The check compares the returned data against the size of regs, rather than the whole regbuf. Do you think this deserves a comment to clarify that?",
      "parentUuid": "61f60714_43c5f6ff",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f1e8b174_36907877",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 230,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T19:57:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e That\u0027s why I added the \"extra\" char in the buffer. The check compares the returned data against the size of regs, rather than the whole regbuf. Do you think this deserves a comment to clarify that?\n\nAh, yes, that’s subtle. Please add a comment.",
      "parentUuid": "cc8083dd_dc372dd6",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e3a514ed_61e114e5",
        "filename": "util/posix/process_info_linux.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 239,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-08T16:47:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This can be simplified to\n\n  is_64_bit_ \u003d iovec.iov_len \u003d\u003d sizeof(regbuf.regs);",
      "revId": "2ae855380b2b4a0eefbd86ad8bb83b47ee6299d9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
